<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="179">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="179">
Body slender, uniformly white, sparsely covered by long and short fine setae, without gill and ocelli (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. First instar nymphs of Microperla brevicauda. A. Habitus, dorsal view, scanning electron microscopy (SEM); B. Habitus, dorsal view, same specimen as in (A), light microscopy; C. Mouth parts, ventral view, SEM; D. Middle leg, SEM. Abbreviations: An, antenna; Ca, cardo; Ce, cercus; Cx, coxa; Fe, femur; Ga, galea; Gl, glossa; H, head; LbP, labial palp; Lr, labrum; Md, mandible; Msn, mesonotum; Mtn, metanotum; Pgl, paraglossa; Pta, pretarsus; Spa, supraanal lobe; St, stipes; Ta, tarsus; Ti, tibia; Tr, trochanter. Scale bars: 100 µm (A, B); 20 µm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.68.65540.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/540150" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">2A, B</figureCitation>
). Head prognathous, subtriangular (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. First instar nymphs of Microperla brevicauda. A. Habitus, dorsal view, scanning electron microscopy (SEM); B. Habitus, dorsal view, same specimen as in (A), light microscopy; C. Mouth parts, ventral view, SEM; D. Middle leg, SEM. Abbreviations: An, antenna; Ca, cardo; Ce, cercus; Cx, coxa; Fe, femur; Ga, galea; Gl, glossa; H, head; LbP, labial palp; Lr, labrum; Md, mandible; Msn, mesonotum; Mtn, metanotum; Pgl, paraglossa; Pta, pretarsus; Spa, supraanal lobe; St, stipes; Ta, tarsus; Ti, tibia; Tr, trochanter. Scale bars: 100 µm (A, B); 20 µm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.68.65540.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/540150" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">2A, B</figureCitation>
). Antenna nine-segmented, longer than two-thirds of body length (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. First instar nymphs of Microperla brevicauda. A. Habitus, dorsal view, scanning electron microscopy (SEM); B. Habitus, dorsal view, same specimen as in (A), light microscopy; C. Mouth parts, ventral view, SEM; D. Middle leg, SEM. Abbreviations: An, antenna; Ca, cardo; Ce, cercus; Cx, coxa; Fe, femur; Ga, galea; Gl, glossa; H, head; LbP, labial palp; Lr, labrum; Md, mandible; Msn, mesonotum; Mtn, metanotum; Pgl, paraglossa; Pta, pretarsus; Spa, supraanal lobe; St, stipes; Ta, tarsus; Ti, tibia; Tr, trochanter. Scale bars: 100 µm (A, B); 20 µm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.68.65540.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/540150" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">2A, B</figureCitation>
; Table 
<tableCitation captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Measurements of the fixed specimens of first instar nymphs of Microperla brevicauda and Yoraperla uenoi." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/E87B748A671E17F6F87255491BD24CB4" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" tableUuid="E87B748A671E17F6F87255491BD24CB4">1</tableCitation>
). Compound eye reddish-black with four ommatidia. Labrum nearly semicircular, covering part of mandible (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. First instar nymphs of Microperla brevicauda. A. Habitus, dorsal view, scanning electron microscopy (SEM); B. Habitus, dorsal view, same specimen as in (A), light microscopy; C. Mouth parts, ventral view, SEM; D. Middle leg, SEM. Abbreviations: An, antenna; Ca, cardo; Ce, cercus; Cx, coxa; Fe, femur; Ga, galea; Gl, glossa; H, head; LbP, labial palp; Lr, labrum; Md, mandible; Msn, mesonotum; Mtn, metanotum; Pgl, paraglossa; Pta, pretarsus; Spa, supraanal lobe; St, stipes; Ta, tarsus; Ti, tibia; Tr, trochanter. Scale bars: 100 µm (A, B); 20 µm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.68.65540.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/540150" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">2C</figureCitation>
). Maxillary coxopodites divided into distal cardo and proximal stipes (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. First instar nymphs of Microperla brevicauda. A. Habitus, dorsal view, scanning electron microscopy (SEM); B. Habitus, dorsal view, same specimen as in (A), light microscopy; C. Mouth parts, ventral view, SEM; D. Middle leg, SEM. Abbreviations: An, antenna; Ca, cardo; Ce, cercus; Cx, coxa; Fe, femur; Ga, galea; Gl, glossa; H, head; LbP, labial palp; Lr, labrum; Md, mandible; Msn, mesonotum; Mtn, metanotum; Pgl, paraglossa; Pta, pretarsus; Spa, supraanal lobe; St, stipes; Ta, tarsus; Ti, tibia; Tr, trochanter. Scale bars: 100 µm (A, B); 20 µm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.68.65540.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/540150" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">2C</figureCitation>
); maxillary palp and endites of maxilla and lateral galea well developed, but mesal lacinia hardly visible externally (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. First instar nymphs of Microperla brevicauda. A. Habitus, dorsal view, scanning electron microscopy (SEM); B. Habitus, dorsal view, same specimen as in (A), light microscopy; C. Mouth parts, ventral view, SEM; D. Middle leg, SEM. Abbreviations: An, antenna; Ca, cardo; Ce, cercus; Cx, coxa; Fe, femur; Ga, galea; Gl, glossa; H, head; LbP, labial palp; Lr, labrum; Md, mandible; Msn, mesonotum; Mtn, metanotum; Pgl, paraglossa; Pta, pretarsus; Spa, supraanal lobe; St, stipes; Ta, tarsus; Ti, tibia; Tr, trochanter. Scale bars: 100 µm (A, B); 20 µm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.68.65540.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/540150" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">2C</figureCitation>
). Labial coxopodites divided into proximal postmentum and distal prementum, but hardly recognizable in fixed specimen (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. First instar nymphs of Microperla brevicauda. A. Habitus, dorsal view, scanning electron microscopy (SEM); B. Habitus, dorsal view, same specimen as in (A), light microscopy; C. Mouth parts, ventral view, SEM; D. Middle leg, SEM. Abbreviations: An, antenna; Ca, cardo; Ce, cercus; Cx, coxa; Fe, femur; Ga, galea; Gl, glossa; H, head; LbP, labial palp; Lr, labrum; Md, mandible; Msn, mesonotum; Mtn, metanotum; Pgl, paraglossa; Pta, pretarsus; Spa, supraanal lobe; St, stipes; Ta, tarsus; Ti, tibia; Tr, trochanter. Scale bars: 100 µm (A, B); 20 µm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.68.65540.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/540150" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">2C</figureCitation>
); labial palp and endites of labium, lateral paraglossa, and mesal glossa well developed (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. First instar nymphs of Microperla brevicauda. A. Habitus, dorsal view, scanning electron microscopy (SEM); B. Habitus, dorsal view, same specimen as in (A), light microscopy; C. Mouth parts, ventral view, SEM; D. Middle leg, SEM. Abbreviations: An, antenna; Ca, cardo; Ce, cercus; Cx, coxa; Fe, femur; Ga, galea; Gl, glossa; H, head; LbP, labial palp; Lr, labrum; Md, mandible; Msn, mesonotum; Mtn, metanotum; Pgl, paraglossa; Pta, pretarsus; Spa, supraanal lobe; St, stipes; Ta, tarsus; Ti, tibia; Tr, trochanter. Scale bars: 100 µm (A, B); 20 µm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.68.65540.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/540150" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">2C</figureCitation>
). Pronotum rectangular, almost same width as the head, and wider than the abdomen (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. First instar nymphs of Microperla brevicauda. A. Habitus, dorsal view, scanning electron microscopy (SEM); B. Habitus, dorsal view, same specimen as in (A), light microscopy; C. Mouth parts, ventral view, SEM; D. Middle leg, SEM. Abbreviations: An, antenna; Ca, cardo; Ce, cercus; Cx, coxa; Fe, femur; Ga, galea; Gl, glossa; H, head; LbP, labial palp; Lr, labrum; Md, mandible; Msn, mesonotum; Mtn, metanotum; Pgl, paraglossa; Pta, pretarsus; Spa, supraanal lobe; St, stipes; Ta, tarsus; Ti, tibia; Tr, trochanter. Scale bars: 100 µm (A, B); 20 µm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.68.65540.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/540150" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">2A</figureCitation>
; Table 
<tableCitation captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Measurements of the fixed specimens of first instar nymphs of Microperla brevicauda and Yoraperla uenoi." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/E87B748A671E17F6F87255491BD24CB4" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" tableUuid="E87B748A671E17F6F87255491BD24CB4">1</tableCitation>
). Lateral margin of mesonotum and metanotum less developed (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. First instar nymphs of Microperla brevicauda. A. Habitus, dorsal view, scanning electron microscopy (SEM); B. Habitus, dorsal view, same specimen as in (A), light microscopy; C. Mouth parts, ventral view, SEM; D. Middle leg, SEM. Abbreviations: An, antenna; Ca, cardo; Ce, cercus; Cx, coxa; Fe, femur; Ga, galea; Gl, glossa; H, head; LbP, labial palp; Lr, labrum; Md, mandible; Msn, mesonotum; Mtn, metanotum; Pgl, paraglossa; Pta, pretarsus; Spa, supraanal lobe; St, stipes; Ta, tarsus; Ti, tibia; Tr, trochanter. Scale bars: 100 µm (A, B); 20 µm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.68.65540.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/540150" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">2A</figureCitation>
). Thoracic appendage consisting of coxa, trochanter, femur, tibia, tarsus with three tarsomeres, and pretarsus with ungues (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. First instar nymphs of Microperla brevicauda. A. Habitus, dorsal view, scanning electron microscopy (SEM); B. Habitus, dorsal view, same specimen as in (A), light microscopy; C. Mouth parts, ventral view, SEM; D. Middle leg, SEM. Abbreviations: An, antenna; Ca, cardo; Ce, cercus; Cx, coxa; Fe, femur; Ga, galea; Gl, glossa; H, head; LbP, labial palp; Lr, labrum; Md, mandible; Msn, mesonotum; Mtn, metanotum; Pgl, paraglossa; Pta, pretarsus; Spa, supraanal lobe; St, stipes; Ta, tarsus; Ti, tibia; Tr, trochanter. Scale bars: 100 µm (A, B); 20 µm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.68.65540.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/540150" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">2D</figureCitation>
); tibia longer than femur (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. First instar nymphs of Microperla brevicauda. A. Habitus, dorsal view, scanning electron microscopy (SEM); B. Habitus, dorsal view, same specimen as in (A), light microscopy; C. Mouth parts, ventral view, SEM; D. Middle leg, SEM. Abbreviations: An, antenna; Ca, cardo; Ce, cercus; Cx, coxa; Fe, femur; Ga, galea; Gl, glossa; H, head; LbP, labial palp; Lr, labrum; Md, mandible; Msn, mesonotum; Mtn, metanotum; Pgl, paraglossa; Pta, pretarsus; Spa, supraanal lobe; St, stipes; Ta, tarsus; Ti, tibia; Tr, trochanter. Scale bars: 100 µm (A, B); 20 µm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.68.65540.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/540150" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">2D</figureCitation>
). Abdominal segments with a row of long fine setae along posterior margin of each tergum (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. First instar nymphs of Microperla brevicauda. A. Habitus, dorsal view, scanning electron microscopy (SEM); B. Habitus, dorsal view, same specimen as in (A), light microscopy; C. Mouth parts, ventral view, SEM; D. Middle leg, SEM. Abbreviations: An, antenna; Ca, cardo; Ce, cercus; Cx, coxa; Fe, femur; Ga, galea; Gl, glossa; H, head; LbP, labial palp; Lr, labrum; Md, mandible; Msn, mesonotum; Mtn, metanotum; Pgl, paraglossa; Pta, pretarsus; Spa, supraanal lobe; St, stipes; Ta, tarsus; Ti, tibia; Tr, trochanter. Scale bars: 100 µm (A, B); 20 µm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.68.65540.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/540150" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">2A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Chloride cells of first instar nymphs of Microperla brevicauda and Yoraperla uenoi, anterior to the left. A. Abdomen of M. brevicauda, lateral view, stained with Mayer's acid haemalum; B, C. Horizontal sections of fifth abdominal segment of M. brevicauda (B) and Y. uenoi (C); D, E. Abdomen of M. brevicauda, lateral view, scanning electron microscopy (SEM), all abdominal segments (D) and enlargement of chloride cells (E); F, G. Abdomen of Y. uenoi, ventrolateral view, SEM, all abdominal segments (F) and enlargement of chloride cells (G). Arrowheads show the chloride cells. Abbreviations: A 1, 2, 3, 5, and 10: first, second, third, fifth and tenth abdominal segments, respectively; Ce, cercus; Mtn, metanotum. Scale bars: 50 µm (A, D, F); 10 µm (B, C, E, G)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.68.65540.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/540152" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">4A</figureCitation>
). Coniform chloride cells approximately 10 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
in diameter and 1 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
in height distributed on lateral side of first nine abdominal segments; one pair on first, eighth, and ninth targa; two pairs on second to seventh segments, i.e., one pair on each of second to seventh terga and sterna (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Chloride cells of first instar nymphs of Microperla brevicauda and Yoraperla uenoi, anterior to the left. A. Abdomen of M. brevicauda, lateral view, stained with Mayer's acid haemalum; B, C. Horizontal sections of fifth abdominal segment of M. brevicauda (B) and Y. uenoi (C); D, E. Abdomen of M. brevicauda, lateral view, scanning electron microscopy (SEM), all abdominal segments (D) and enlargement of chloride cells (E); F, G. Abdomen of Y. uenoi, ventrolateral view, SEM, all abdominal segments (F) and enlargement of chloride cells (G). Arrowheads show the chloride cells. Abbreviations: A 1, 2, 3, 5, and 10: first, second, third, fifth and tenth abdominal segments, respectively; Ce, cercus; Mtn, metanotum. Scale bars: 50 µm (A, D, F); 10 µm (B, C, E, G)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.68.65540.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/540152" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">4A, B, D, E</figureCitation>
). Less sclerotized supraanal lobe on hind margin of tenth tergum (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. First instar nymphs of Microperla brevicauda. A. Habitus, dorsal view, scanning electron microscopy (SEM); B. Habitus, dorsal view, same specimen as in (A), light microscopy; C. Mouth parts, ventral view, SEM; D. Middle leg, SEM. Abbreviations: An, antenna; Ca, cardo; Ce, cercus; Cx, coxa; Fe, femur; Ga, galea; Gl, glossa; H, head; LbP, labial palp; Lr, labrum; Md, mandible; Msn, mesonotum; Mtn, metanotum; Pgl, paraglossa; Pta, pretarsus; Spa, supraanal lobe; St, stipes; Ta, tarsus; Ti, tibia; Tr, trochanter. Scale bars: 100 µm (A, B); 20 µm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.68.65540.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/540150" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">2A</figureCitation>
). Cerci four-segmented, with a crown of long and short fine setae on posterior margin of first three segments; short fine setae at apex of fourth segment (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. First instar nymphs of Microperla brevicauda. A. Habitus, dorsal view, scanning electron microscopy (SEM); B. Habitus, dorsal view, same specimen as in (A), light microscopy; C. Mouth parts, ventral view, SEM; D. Middle leg, SEM. Abbreviations: An, antenna; Ca, cardo; Ce, cercus; Cx, coxa; Fe, femur; Ga, galea; Gl, glossa; H, head; LbP, labial palp; Lr, labrum; Md, mandible; Msn, mesonotum; Mtn, metanotum; Pgl, paraglossa; Pta, pretarsus; Spa, supraanal lobe; St, stipes; Ta, tarsus; Ti, tibia; Tr, trochanter. Scale bars: 100 µm (A, B); 20 µm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.68.65540.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/540150" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">2A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
